The paper deals with the detection of facial forgery in digital images and videos using deep learning techniques, specifically the separable convolutional neural network (CNN) and image segmentation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the ethical and legal challenges posed by deepfake technology, which could be classified under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. The proposed solution involves using deep learning algorithms, which could also be classified under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
